OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1773792182
OL,3,CAstronomers 'alarmed' by plans to use
OL,4,Cspace mirrors to light Earth at night
OL,6,FBritish astronomers have said they are
OL,7,F"alarmed" by a US company's proposals
OL,8,Fto launch space mirrors to reflect
OL,9,Fsunlight to Earth at night.
OL,11,FCalifornia-based start up Reflect
OL,12,FOrbital plans to launch satellites
OL,13,Fwith mirrors attached to them later
OL,14,Fthis year in order to deliver sunlight
OL,15,Fon demand.
OL,17,FThe company says the lights are
OL,18,Fdimmable, highly localised, and easy
OL,19,Fto relocate when needed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/5
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
